---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<BaseLayout title="Introduction">
  <h1>Introduction</h1>
  <p>A minimal, dark-accent design system inspired by modern SaaS interfaces like Clerk.com.</p>

  <h2>What is Stoneware?</h2>
  <p>Stoneware is a CSS-first design system that provides everything you need to build clean, professional interfaces. It includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Design Tokens</strong> - CSS custom properties for colors, typography, spacing, shadows, and more</li>
    <li><strong>Component Classes</strong> - Pre-built styles for buttons, inputs, cards, modals, and other UI elements</li>
    <li><strong>Utility Classes</strong> - Helpers for layout, spacing, and common patterns</li>
    <li><strong>Dark Mode</strong> - Full dark mode support via <code>data-theme="dark"</code></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Design Philosophy</h2>
  <p>Stoneware follows these core principles:</p>

  <h3>Clean</h3>
  <p>Remove visual noise and embrace generous whitespace. Let everything breathe.</p>

  <h3>Dark Accents</h3>
  <p>Primary actions use near-black (<code>#18181b</code>), not bright colors.

  <h3>Subtle Shadows</h3>
  <p>Please don't use these, but if you need them they are light and they create depth without distraction.</p>

  <h3>Smooth Transitions</h3>
  <p>Nothing too fancy. Less is more</p>

  <h2>Quick Example</h2>

  <div class="preview">
    <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; flex-wrap: wrap;">
      <button class="sw-btn sw-btn-primary">Primary Action</button>
      <button class="sw-btn sw-btn-secondary">Secondary</button>
      <button class="sw-btn sw-btn-ghost">Ghost</button>
    </div>
  </div>

  <pre><code set:html={`&lt;button class="sw-btn sw-btn-primary"&gt;Primary Action&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button class="sw-btn sw-btn-secondary"&gt;Secondary&lt;/button&gt;
&lt;button class="sw-btn sw-btn-ghost"&gt;Ghost&lt;/button&gt;`}></code></pre>

  <h2>Next Steps</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><a href={`${base}getting-started/installation`}>Installation</a> - Get Stoneware into your project</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}foundations/colors`}>Colors</a> - Explore the color palette</li>
    <li><a href={`${base}components/buttons`}>Buttons</a> - Start building with components</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
